CC   -!- FUNCTION: Calcium-dependent cell-adhesion protein (PubMed:21115806).
CC       Essential for the early stages of neurulation in the anterior neural
CC       plate (PubMed:19615992). Shows little cell adhesion activity on its own
CC       but exhibits robust homophilic cell adhesion when in a complex with
CC       cadherin cdh2 and appears to mediate the adhesion while cdh2 acts as a
CC       cell adhesion cofactor in the complex (PubMed:21115806,
CC       PubMed:22184198, PubMed:33004519). Functions with cdh2 to coordinate
CC       cell adhesion and cell movements during neurulation (PubMed:21115806).
CC       Contributes to neural progenitor cell patterning with cdh2 by promoting
CC       homophilic cell interactions (PubMed:33004519). Regulates the columnar
CC       organization of neurons in the optic tectum (PubMed:26598617).
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:19615992, ECO:0000269|PubMed:21115806,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:22184198, ECO:0000269|PubMed:26598617,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:33004519}.
CC   -!- SUBUNIT: Homodimer; antiparallel (PubMed:27787195). Interacts with
CC       cadherin cdh2; the interaction confers robust cell adhesion activity on
CC       pcdh19 (PubMed:21115806, PubMed:22184198).
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:21115806, ECO:0000269|PubMed:22184198,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:27787195}.

CC   -!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: In the embryo, strongly expressed in the developing
CC       nervous system (PubMed:19615992). At 12 hours post fertilization (hpf),
CC       shows a segmental expression pattern in the anterior third of the
CC       neural keel with strong expression in the presumptive forebrain,
CC       cerebellum/rhombomere 1 and rhombomere 4 (PubMed:19757381). By 24 hpf,
CC       expressed widely in the brain and spinal cord with higher expression
CC       levels in the ventral telencephalon, dorsal and central thalamus, optic
CC       tectum, central tegmentum, cerebellum and dorsolateral regions of the
CC       hindbrain (PubMed:19757381). As development proceeds, expression
CC       becomes restricted to the dorsal and/or lateral regions of the central
CC       nervous system (PubMed:19757381). Not detected in the spinal cord of
CC       two- and three-day old embryos (PubMed:19757381). Expressed in the eye
CC       primordium, developing retina, lens and otic vesicle (PubMed:19757381).
CC       Expressed in the larval optic tectum at 4 days post-fertilization where
CC       it localizes in discrete columns of neurons (PubMed:26598617).
CC       Expressed throughout the adult brain with strong expression in the
CC       ventromedial telencephalon, periventricular regions of the thalamus and
CC       anterior hypothalamus, stratum periventriculare of the optic tectum,
CC       dorsal tegmental nucleus, granular regions of the cerebellar body and
CC       valvula, and superficial layers of the facial and vagal lobes
CC       (PubMed:25612302). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:19615992,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:19757381, ECO:0000269|PubMed:25612302,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:26598617}.
CC   -!- DEVELOPMENTAL STAGE: Undetectable in unfertilized eggs and in embryos
CC       at 2 and 4 hours post-fertilization (hpf) (PubMed:35460869). Also not
CC       detected in embryos at 6 hpf (PubMed:19757381). Expression is detected
CC       in the embryo at 12 hpf (PubMed:19757381). Expression is also detected
